ZH: 他的轻率行为导致了一个严重的事故。
EN: His reckless behavior caused a serious accident.

ZH: 不要因为一时冲动而做出轻率的决定。
EN: Don't make hasty decisions out of impulse.

ZH: 她的轻率态度让我们很生气。
EN: Her careless attitude made us angry.

ZH: 他的轻率言行总是给人留下坏印象。
EN: His thoughtless words and actions always leave a bad impression.

ZH: 这个决定太轻率了，我们需要更多时间考虑。
EN: This decision is too hasty; we need more time to consider.

ZH: 驾车时不要过于轻率，要注意安全。
EN: Do not drive recklessly, pay attention to safety.

ZH: 他的轻率承诺让她失望了。
EN: His rash promise disappointed her.

ZH: 轻率地相信他人很容易导致被骗。
EN: Believing in others recklessly can easily lead to deception.

ZH: 这种轻率的行为很容易导致事态失控。
EN: Such reckless behavior can easily lead to things spiraling out of control.

ZH: 不要轻率地相信谣言，要保持冷静。
EN: Do not blindly believe rumors, stay calm.

ZH: 她对待学业过于轻率，请她认真对待。
EN: She is too careless about her studies, ask her to take it seriously.

ZH: 轻率的评论会伤害他人的感情。
EN: Thoughtless comments can hurt others' feelings.

ZH: 我们需要谨慎对待而不是轻率行事。
EN: We need to act cautiously instead of being reckless.

ZH: 这个极端的决定过于轻率了。
EN: This extreme decision is too hasty.

ZH: 请不要轻率地打断别人的发言。
EN: Please do not interrupt others' speech arbitrarily.

ZH: 他很轻率地拒绝了那个机会，现在后悔了。
EN: He recklessly turned down that opportunity and now regrets it.

ZH: 这个项目还需要仔细研究，不要轻率下结论。
EN: This project still needs careful research, do not rush to conclusions.

ZH: 他的轻率态度使得合作失败了。
EN: His careless attitude led to the failure of the cooperation.

ZH: 犯罪时请不要轻率留下证据。
EN: Do not leave evidence recklessly when committing a crime.

ZH: 考试前的轻率复习会影响成绩。
EN: Careless revision before an exam will affect the results.

ZH: 这次会议需要认真讨论，不要轻率做决定。
EN: This meeting requires serious discussion, do not make hasty decisions.
